	<div id="idc8e" class="post">
		<h2 class="title"><span class="image-wrapper"><img height="45" alt="Amanda Hesser's Lemon Chicken" width="531" class="title" src="../../../resources/net.databinder.components.RenderedLabel/c8d7e19"/><span class="title">Amanda Hesser&#039;s Lemon Chicken</span></span></h2>
		<div class="byline"><span>
			<span>By <span class="alias">Leland</span>, <span>on April 10, 2006</span></span>
			<span id="idc8f" class="tags">
					{&nbsp;<span><a href="../../../eat/tag/home%20cooking/#selected-tag"><span>home cooking</span></a></span>&nbsp;}
			</span>
		</span></div>
		<div><p>Let&#8217;s all thank <a href="http://wednesdaychef.typepad.com">Wednesday Chef</a> for sharing Amanda Hesser&#8217;s excellent <a href="http://wednesdaychef.typepad.com/the_wednesday_chef/2006/03/imbb_24_amanda_.html">recipe</a> for lemon chicken. I made it because she described it as &#8220;the dish that made [my boyfriend] look up from his plate a few days ago and proclaim firmly that this was the best thing I&#8217;d ever cooked for him.&#8221; What is it about lemon chicken that drives men crazy? Nathan&#8217;s little head almost exploded from all the crème fraîche goodness.</p>


	<p style="float:center"><img src="/pictures/lemonchicken.jpg" alt="" /></p>


	<p>There&#8217;s nothing to this recipe. It seems the key is to brown and season the chicken extremely well, and to use enough real crème fraîche and fresh lemon juice. It&#8217;s easy, it&#8217;s cheap, and it&#8217;s delicious.</p></div>
	</div>
